<h2>Charter | Team 3 ITC515</h2>
<p>Draft 001: July 19, 2015</p>
<h4>Team Members</h4>
<ul>
<li>Andrew M.</li>
<li>Mark B.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Purpose</h4>
<p>This team has come together to complete the requirements for ITC515 with the following intentions:</p>
<ul>
<li>to learn how to function as a team in a software development environment</li>
<li>to participate in code reviews, testing, and debugging to the benefit of the overall project and to learn from each other in those contexts</li>
<li>IN SHORT: colloborate and make better software</li>
</ul>
<h4>Vision</h4>
<ul>
<li>we want to make great software... on time... on budget... but most importantly (in the context of ITC515) we want to do so in the most effiecient way possible.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Values</h4>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">What are the most important values that we will adopt to guide our </span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">actions and decisions as a team (e.g. integrity)? </span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">What are the specific behaviors that describe each value? (e.g. integrity = </span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">we do what we say we will do)</span></li>
<li>we value expertise and experience</li>
<li>we value mutual respect and listening</li>
<li>we value frequent communication</li>
<li>we value timeliness</li>
<li>we value decisiveness</li>
<li>we value collaboration and peer review</li>
</ul>
<h4>Goals</h4>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">What are our shared team goals and deliverables? </span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">How will we measure our success?</span></li>
<li>Our aim is to understand how to properly implement a software QA process so that shipping time decreases and refactoring in later versions is easy and obvious</li>
</ul>
<h4>Roles and Responsibilities</h4>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">What are our individual skills and functional areas of responsibility? </span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">How do our individual accountabilities impact each other?</span></li>
<li>We will develop TK using TK</li>
<li>Andrew's roll will be TK</li>
<li>Mark's roll will be TK</li>
</ul>
<h4>Expectations</h4>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">What specific behaviors do we want and expect of each other? </span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">What behaviors would negatively impact our working relationship? </span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">What is the best way to give each other feedback?</span></li>
<li>We expect everyone to do their part</li>
<li>We expect everyone to be courteous</li>
<li>We expect everyone to stay in touch</li>
</ul>
<h4>Operating Procedures</h4>
<p>Here are our ground rules for communication</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">What is the best way to communicate with each other and keep each other informed? (e.g. voicemail, e-mail)</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;"> How quickly do we agree to return phone calls and e-mail?</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;"> How and what will we communicate to our key constituents?</span></li>
<li>We will...</li>
<li>We will...</li>
<li>We will...</li>
</ul>
<p>Here are our ground rules for making decisions..</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">What will be our primary decision-making method? (e.g. consensus)</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">What decisions will we make on our own?</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">What decisions will require agreement among all team members?</span></li>
</ul>
<p>Here are our ground rules for meetings</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">How often will we meet? For how long? When &amp; where?</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">How will we develop meeting agendas?</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">Who will lead or facilitate our meetings?</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">How will we keep track of our decisions and agreed-upon actions?</span></li>
<li>We will meet weekly at TK</li>
<li>We will use TK methodolgy</li>
<li>We will use TK tools</li>
</ul>
<p>Here is how we expect to resolve conflicts...</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">How will we resolve disagreements?</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">How will we handle if we do not follow through with our agreements?</span></li>
<li>We will...</li>
<li>We will...</li>
<li>We will...</li>
</ul>
<p>Reflection</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #ff0000;">How and when will we evaluate our team performance?</span></li>
</ul>
